Source: tty-egpf-monitor
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Adrian <adrian@example.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 13), clang, make, libelf-dev, zlib1g-dev, pkg-config, build-essential, linux-headers-generic, libbpf-dev, bpftool | linux-tools-common

Package: tty-egpf-monitord
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, adduser
Description: eBPF serial monitoring daemon with HTTP API
 A sophisticated real-time serial port monitoring tool that combines
 the power of eBPF (extended Berkeley Packet Filter) with intelligent
 state management to provide comprehensive visibility into TTY device
 activity. Perfect for debugging, reverse engineering, and monitoring
 serial communications.
 .
 Features:
  * Dual-mode operation (active/passive monitoring)
  * Real-time data capture and analysis
  * eBPF-based packet filtering
  * Comprehensive logging and reporting
  * Support for various serial protocols
  * Listens on Unix socket /run/tty-egpf-monitord.sock

Package: tty-egpf-monitor-cli
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: CLI for tty-egpf-monitord HTTP API
 Lightweight command line client to manage the local daemon and list/add
 monitored ports, suitable for container environments.
